<text>The Damping Tool

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

A damping force on an object is a force that is proportional to the speed of the object, in the direction opposite to which it is moving. As a result, when it is applied, it will slow down the object. The faster the object is moving, the greater the damping force is.

You may practice using the Damping Tool with the following model:

 
&#12304;This is an embedded model container.&#12305;

Script support

The damp command can be used to apply a damping force with a specified friction coefficient to the selected particles.

